 MF = 2 Resonance Parameters                                      5843 1451
  A set of Reich-Moore resonance parameters (LRF=3, LCOMP=1) was  5843 1451
  evaluated by fitting transmission and capture yield data        5843 1451
  recently measured by Guber[1] as well as the recommended        5843 1451
  thermal constants. The fit was performed by the Bayesian R-     5843 1451
  matrix methodology implemented in the SAMMY code[2] starting    5843 1451
  from a revised set of ENDF/B-VIII.0 resonance parameter[3].     5843 1451
  Due to the lack of experimental details, other available        5843 1451
  measured data were not included in the R-matrix fit. A more     5843 1451
  detailed description of the reasoning behind this can be found  5843 1451
  in [4]. Only their overall agreement with the evaluted          5843 1451
  parameters was checked. Additionally, the mass was updated to   5843 1451
  be in agreement with [5].                                       5843 1451
                                                                  5843 1451
  An error was found in the 1-2 keV region where the 1.15 keV and 5843 1451
  1.65 keV resonances were input as s-wave resonances & had an    5843 1451
  elastic scattering width 3 orders of magnitude larger than      5843 1451
  originally reported. It is believed that the 1.15 keV resonance 5843 1451
  is a transcription error from the original sources [6] to the   5843 1451
  Atlas [7], while the 1.65 keV resonance is a transcription      5843 1451
  error by the original authors [8].                              5843 1451
                                                                  5843 1451
  Resonance parameters were found up to 200 keV, but the level    5843 1451
  spacing indicated that there are missing levels in the          5843 1451
  experimental data above ~26 keV. As such, the upper energy      5843 1451
  limit was increased from 13 keV to 26 keV. To describe the      5843 1451
  contribution of the external resonance levels, two energy       5843 1451
  levels above 200 keV and two levels below zero were defined.    5843 1451
  Additionally, a third negative resonance level was added to     5843 1451
  better fit the thermal values.                                  5843 1451
                                                                  5843 1451
  Based of the chi-squared metric, several energy levels were     5843 1451
  changed from s-wave to p-wave to better agree with the measured 5843 1451
  data. Additional p-waves were added where they could be seen in 5843 1451
  the new measurements. The unresolved resonance parameters were  5843 1451
  kept the same from the previous evaluation, except for removing 5843 1451
  the first block of parameters from 13 - 26 keV.                 5843 1451
